description: This is a market on predicting the statements made by Trump during his town hall scheduled for Warren, Michigan, on September 27, 2024.

markets.description:
Donald Trump has scheduled to hold a town hall on September 27 in Warren, Michigan (see: https://event.donaldjtrump.com/events/president-donald-j-trump-to-host-a-townhall-in-warren-michigan). 

This market will resolve to "Yes" if Trump says "inflation" 10 or more times during their appearance at this event. Otherwise, the market will resolve to "No".

Any usage of the word regardless of context will count toward the resolution of this market.

Pluralization/possessive of the word will count toward the resolution of this market, however other forms will NOT count.

Compound words will count as long as "inflation" is part of the compound word and references the meaning which refers to increases in costs of goods and services.

If this candidate does not appear at this event, or if the event is otherwise cancelled or delayed beyond September 27, this market will resolve to "No".

The resolution source will be the video of the speech.
markets.question: Will Donald Trump say "inflation" 10 or more times during his Michigan town hall?
